We recommended that the Management initiate the creation of the additional mandatory LDRRMO staff for administration and training, research and planning; and operations and warning through any or a combination of the following options as provided under NDRRMC-DILG-DBM-CSC Joint Memorandum Circular              No. 2014-1 and R.A. No. 10121:

Designation or assignment of personnel of LGU to LDRRMO in concurrent capacities with their existing positions;
Reassignment of personnel of the LGU to the LDRRMO;
Full-time or part-time detail of existing personnel of other government agencies to the LDRRMO; and/or,
Transfer of existing vacant positions from other units to the LDRRMO. Accordingly, such vacant positions shall be abolished and positions appropriate to the LDRRMO shall be created.

We recommended Management the following:
Strictly comply the accounting guidelines prescribed under Sections 5.1.10 and 5.1.12 of COA Circular No. 2012-002 so as to fairly present the Trust Liability-DRRMF (Trust Fund books) and Subsidy to Other Funds (General Fund book);
Ensure that the unexpended balance of QRF and the DRRMF-MOOE at the end of the year will be transferred to the Special Trust Fund Account and will be recorded under the Trust-Liabilities-DRRMF account;
Ensure that Continuing Appropriations/Capital Outlay of DRRMF will continue to be recorded under the General Fund books until the projects funded therefor are completed and should never be transferred to STF;
Set-up and maintain subsidiary ledgers for the special trust fund for unutilized DRRMF by year of transfer, receipts of NDRRMF by transferring agency, DRRMF from other LGUs by LGU, and other sources by donor in order to readily determine the balances of transfers/receipts; and
With the updated subsidiary ledger per year, reconcile and correct the Notes to Financial Statements by reflecting the correct balances of special trust fund by year.

We recommended Management to direct the Municipal Accountant the following remedial measures to attain fairness of presentation of the Cash and Cash Equivalent, in conformity with Paragraph 76 of IPSAS 1;

To discontinue the inclusion of Undelivered and Staled Checks among its Outstanding Checks in preparing its Bank reconciliation Statements; and 
To draw JEV to restore the cash and liabilities pertaining to the stale and undelivered checks.

